50|$|Where {{interlockings}} {{are closely}} placed, a Starting <b>signal</b> <b>arm</b> may be fitted above a Distant <b>signal</b> <b>arm.</b> In {{this case the}} Starting arm can be placed at Stop and display a red light. As the lower Distant <b>signal</b> <b>arm</b> cannot be cleared while the upper arm is at Stop the signal will show two red lights. The basis for Double Light signalling was thus established by a sequence of Distant and two-arm signals, {{so that it was}} then possible to encounter a signal showing two green lights (Clear), followed by a green light over a red light (Caution) then one or two red lights (Stop).|$|E
